      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "inverse of the shortest duration of a signal element",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "The term \"modulation rate\" is used in conventional\ntelegraphy and data transmission. In isochronous\ndigital transmission, the term \"line digit rate\" is\ngenerally used.\n\nstem:[1 \" Bd\" = s^{-1}]\n\nBaud is a special name for the second to the power of\nminus one for this quantity.\n\nThe baud may be combined with prefixes, for example\nkilobaud, symbol kBd, megabaud, symbol MBd.\n\nSee <<iec60050-704,droploc%locality:item=\"704-17-03\">>.\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-s^{-1}"
        },
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-Bd"
        }
      ],
